<p class=""><h1>Key Challenges in the Nicorandil Tablets Market</h1><p>The <strong>Nicorandil tablets market</strong> faces several key challenges that could hinder its growth potential. One major challenge is the <strong>regulatory scrutiny</strong> surrounding the drug. Regulatory bodies require extensive clinical trials and comprehensive data on safety and efficacy, which can be both time-consuming and costly. Furthermore, the need for compliance with evolving regulations can create barriers for manufacturers, particularly smaller firms.</p><p>Another challenge is the <strong>competition from alternative therapies</strong>. With the rising availability of new medications and treatment options for angina and other cardiovascular diseases, Nicorandil must compete against both established and emerging therapies. This competitive pressure can lead to price erosion and impact profit margins for manufacturers.</p><p>Additionally, <strong>side effects and safety concerns</strong> associated with Nicorandil have been frequently reported, including headaches and gastrointestinal issues. Such adverse effects may deter both healthcare providers and patients from choosing this treatment over alternatives, impacting its market adoption.</p><p>Finally, the <strong>fluctuating raw material costs</strong> can pose challenges in maintaining profitability. As global supply chains continue to be affected by geopolitical tensions and economic shifts, the costs for active pharmaceutical ingredients (APIs) can vary significantly, impacting the production of Nicorandil tablets.</p><h1>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Nicorandil Tablets Market</h1><p>Despite these challenges, the Nicorandil tablets market presents several promising growth opportunities. The increasing prevalence of cardiovascular diseases globally serves as a significant driver for demand. As populations age and lifestyle-related health issues rise, there is a growing need for effective therapeutic options like Nic